  "prompt": "How much does it cost to attend a TED talk?",
  "response": "The cost of attending a TED Talk can vary significantly depending on the specific event and its location. Generally, attending the flagship TED Conference, which is held annually in Vancouver, is quite expensive, with ticket prices often starting at several thousand dollars. For instance, a standard pass might cost around $5,000 to $10,000 USD. There are also other tiers of passes that can be even more expensive, offering additional benefits and networking opportunities.\n\nHowever, there are also TEDx events, which are independently organized and held in various locations around the world. The cost for TEDx events can vary widely; some are free to attend, while others might charge a modest fee ranging from $20 to $100 or more, depending on the scope and nature of the event.\n\nPrices and availability can change, so it's always a good idea to check the official TED or TEDx event websites for the most current information regarding ticket prices and registration details.",
